TopicTitle: [SOLVED, NOT A BUG] Galaxies Unbound: A Stellar Odyssey not adding stars/planets/moons (installed with CKAN latest version)

Articles.Content:
EDIT: I didn't install any star system mods, this problem is solved.

I installed the mod Galaxies Unbound: A Stellar Odyssey using CKAN as well as other mods such as Scatterer and Far Future Technologies recently. The Galaxies Unbound mod is definitely installed as it changed the loading screen and CKAN displays it as installed, but I either can't find the other stars in the tracking station or map view or they weren't added at all. Does anybody know why this is or am I just not understanding how to find the stars in the tracking station? This was done on KSP 1.12.3 with the latest version of CKAN as of writing this. Thanks!

Edited May 3, 2023 by I Exist
Did you install any of the actual planet packs?
No, I just installed the base mod. Let me open CKAN and see if that fixes things.
